Plug-in name: Loop
Plug-in shortname: loop
Description: Find maximum number of iterations in loops

Most options of the form '-loop-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-loop-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-loop               Launch loop analysis (opposite option is -no-loop)

*** DEBUG

-loop-debug <n>     level of debug for plug-in Loop (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-loop-help          help of plug-in Loop
-loop-h             alias for option -loop-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-loop-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Loop to a file. <K> is a
                    combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -loop-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-loop-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -loop-msg-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -loop-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-loop-verbose <n>   level of verbosity for plug-in Loop (default to 1)
-loop-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category <k1>
                    to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -loop-warn-key help to get
                    a list of available categories, and * to enable all
                    categories. Possible statuses are inactive, feedback,
                    warning, error, abort, feedback-once, warning-once,
                    error-once. Defaults to warning. (preferably use
                    -loop-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
